* Generally putting generated stuff to src isn&#39;t a good idea. Better leave the default (in this case target/generated-sources/jaxb).
   * You would have to explicitly exclude it from versioning,
   * mvn clean wouldn&#39;t remove it by default.
* Also you should be aware that files within src/main/resources would be automatically added to your JAR file. May be you intend to use the schema files for runtime validation of incoming XML. Then this would be ok. The bindings files are for code generation only. You will never need them within your JAR file.
* Instead of telling xjc to which package you want to generate your classes by a property in the POM you should better use the bindings customization. This has the advantage that everything affecting your code is in one place. Furthermore for multiple schemas you would have to add more executions to your POM vs. adding another bindings definition to your bindings file.

```
&lt;jxb:bindings schemaLocation=&quot;../schema/fe2_flux_generique.xsd&quot;&gt;
	&lt;jxb:schemaBindings&gt;
		&lt;jxb:package name=&quot;fr.icdc.dei.ddr.fe2.xml.domain&quot;/&gt;
	&lt;/jxb:schemaBindings&gt;
&lt;/jxb:bindings&gt;
```

